Bharat Petroleum Seeks Low-Sulfur February Crude in Tender

-- B y   S h e r r y   S u
-- 
2011-12-13T15:35:41Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-12-13/bharat-petroleum-seeks-low-sulfur-february-crude-in-tender-1-.html
Bharat Petroleum Corp.,  India ’s
second-largest state-run oil refiner, issued a tender seeking to
buy low-sulfur crude for loading from Feb. 1 to Feb. 15,
according to tender documents obtained by Bloomberg News.  Last month, the company bought 1 million barrels each of
Nigerian Qua Iboe and Erha crude for January from Vitol Group.  Details of the Mumbai-based refiner’s requirements are:  To contact the reporter on this story:
